voice_to_text: There is something so wrong about this video and also a similar video that this influencer has posted and it's really pissing me off. Us women who are into sports, who love watching football, who love watching racing, F1, all of that. Us women, we have gotten so many comments thrown at us the last couple of years and even before that of oh, it's a male dominated sports, it's only for men, you only watch for the hot drivers or the hot players and everything. We have been getting those kinds of comments from men for years. Just because we like a sport, just because we like watching football, we like watching racing. And sure, there are probably some girls or women out there who only watch because of the hard men that are doing the sport, but the majority of the industry of women in motorsport, women in football, we watch it because we love watching the sport. And in both sports, we have just gone to a point where it has been more accepted and more generalize for women to also be able to love the sports for the sport, more women getting opportunities in like women's football or F1 academy in the engineering part of F1. So for an influencer who got invited to watch the football, to watch the racing, make a video saying the contrary that oh, she's only there to watch the hot player, she's only there to watch the hot drivers because She's an influencer making these videos. She's gonna have people generalize her videos to the wider community of women in motorsport and women in football, women in sports in general.
